<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="356" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1038,2037]" pageId="3" pageNumber="356">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1038,1064]" pageId="3" pageNumber="356">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[282,373,1038,1064]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="356">Female.</emphasis>
Malar space 0.8× eye height (
<figureCitation box="[720,801,1038,1065]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1919,1943]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,453,1896]" captionTargetId="figure-140@4.[151,1435,453,1896]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1a–f. Chalcis boi sp. nov., holotype female: a, habitus, lateral, b, habitus, dorsal; c, head, frontal; d, head, lateral; e, protarsal claw; f, metafemur and metatibia, outer face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296701" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4296701/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="356">Fig. 1c</figureCitation>
); ovipositor sheath obliquely truncate apically and with some long setae (
<figureCitation box="[347,431,1074,1101]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1169,1193]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1145]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1435,181,1145]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2a–d. Chalcis boi sp. nov., holotype female: a, metatarsus, lateral; b, propodeum; c, gaster, lateral; d, ovipositor sheath, lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296703" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4296703/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="356">Fig. 2d</figureCitation>
); protarsal claws only slightly curved, ventrally with 3 basal spines followed by 2 curved setae (
<figureCitation box="[222,302,1110,1137]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1919,1943]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,453,1896]" captionTargetId="figure-140@4.[151,1435,453,1896]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1a–f. Chalcis boi sp. nov., holotype female: a, habitus, lateral, b, habitus, dorsal; c, head, frontal; d, head, lateral; e, protarsal claw; f, metafemur and metatibia, outer face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296701" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4296701/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="356">Fig. 1e</figureCitation>
); metatarsomere 5 slightly longer than any of tarsomeres 1–4 (
<figureCitation box="[1006,1088,1110,1137]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1169,1193]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1145]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1435,181,1145]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2a–d. Chalcis boi sp. nov., holotype female: a, metatarsus, lateral; b, propodeum; c, gaster, lateral; d, ovipositor sheath, lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296703" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4296703/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="356">Fig. 2a</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="357" pageId="3" pageNumber="356" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1038,2037]" pageId="3" pageNumber="356">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1146,1172]" pageId="3" pageNumber="356">Description</emphasis>
. FEMALE. Length 
<quantity box="[576,669,1147,1173]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.8" pageId="3" pageNumber="356" unit="mm" value="8.8">8.8 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis box="[683,748,1146,1172]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="356">Color</emphasis>
: Predominantly black, but with yellow, reddish-brown and golden-brown areas (
<figureCitation box="[389,457,1182,1209]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1919,1943]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,453,1896]" captionTargetId="figure-140@4.[151,1435,453,1896]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1a–f. Chalcis boi sp. nov., holotype female: a, habitus, lateral, b, habitus, dorsal; c, head, frontal; d, head, lateral; e, protarsal claw; f, metafemur and metatibia, outer face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296701" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4296701/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="356">Figs 1</figureCitation>
a–c, f), as follows. The following yellow: a round spot on parascrobal area (
<figureCitation box="[1320,1401,1182,1209]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1919,1943]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,453,1896]" captionTargetId="figure-140@4.[151,1435,453,1896]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1a–f. Chalcis boi sp. nov., holotype female: a, habitus, lateral, b, habitus, dorsal; c, head, frontal; d, head, lateral; e, protarsal claw; f, metafemur and metatibia, outer face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296701" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4296701/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="356">Fig. 1c</figureCitation>
), a narrow basal band on protibia, first metafemoral tooth (
<figureCitation box="[771,848,1218,1245]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1919,1943]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,453,1896]" captionTargetId="figure-140@4.[151,1435,453,1896]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1a–f. Chalcis boi sp. nov., holotype female: a, habitus, lateral, b, habitus, dorsal; c, head, frontal; d, head, lateral; e, protarsal claw; f, metafemur and metatibia, outer face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296701" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4296701/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="356">Fig. 1f</figureCitation>
), metatibial spine (
<figureCitation box="[1063,1140,1218,1245]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1919,1943]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,453,1896]" captionTargetId="figure-140@4.[151,1435,453,1896]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1a–f. Chalcis boi sp. nov., holotype female: a, habitus, lateral, b, habitus, dorsal; c, head, frontal; d, head, lateral; e, protarsal claw; f, metafemur and metatibia, outer face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296701" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4296701/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="356">Fig. 1f</figureCitation>
), dorsal and posterolateral face of petiole, a transverse, short, medially interrupted band on Gt1, a spot on submedian area of Gt1 (
<figureCitation box="[1320,1402,1254,1281]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1169,1193]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1145]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1435,181,1145]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2a–d. Chalcis boi sp. nov., holotype female: a, metatarsus, lateral; b, propodeum; c, gaster, lateral; d, ovipositor sheath, lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296703" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4296703/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="356">Fig. 2c</figureCitation>
), a transverse band on Gt2 through Gt7+8. The following reddish-brown: ocelli, labrum, mandibles, maxillary palps and labial palps, protibia anteriorly, anterior half of mesotibia, and metafemur from the base through first tooth (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1169,1193]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1145]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1435,181,1145]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2a–d. Chalcis boi sp. nov., holotype female: a, metatarsus, lateral; b, propodeum; c, gaster, lateral; d, ovipositor sheath, lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296703" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4296703/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="356">Fig. 2f</figureCitation>
) and a small internal spot next to apex. Tegula, tarsi and a sub-basal portion of metatibia golden-brown. Wings infuscate (
<figureCitation box="[267,381,1398,1425]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1919,1943]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,453,1896]" captionTargetId="figure-140@4.[151,1435,453,1896]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1a–f. Chalcis boi sp. nov., holotype female: a, habitus, lateral, b, habitus, dorsal; c, head, frontal; d, head, lateral; e, protarsal claw; f, metafemur and metatibia, outer face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296701" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4296701/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="356">Figs 1a, b</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1038,2037]" pageId="3" pageNumber="356">
<emphasis box="[199,260,1434,1460]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="356">Head</emphasis>
. Lower face bulging above clypeus (
<figureCitation box="[669,749,1434,1461]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1919,1943]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,453,1896]" captionTargetId="figure-140@4.[151,1435,453,1896]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1a–f. Chalcis boi sp. nov., holotype female: a, habitus, lateral, b, habitus, dorsal; c, head, frontal; d, head, lateral; e, protarsal claw; f, metafemur and metatibia, outer face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296701" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4296701/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="356">Fig. 1d</figureCitation>
), with elongate umbilicate fovea enclosed by diagonal irregular carinae (
<figureCitation box="[284,365,1470,1497]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1919,1943]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,453,1896]" captionTargetId="figure-140@4.[151,1435,453,1896]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1a–f. Chalcis boi sp. nov., holotype female: a, habitus, lateral, b, habitus, dorsal; c, head, frontal; d, head, lateral; e, protarsal claw; f, metafemur and metatibia, outer face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296701" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4296701/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="356">Fig. 1c</figureCitation>
); parascrobal area densely foveate, interstices raised as irregular diagonal rugae, with a median intumescence, malar space 0.80× eye height (
<figureCitation box="[667,748,1506,1533]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1919,1943]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,453,1896]" captionTargetId="figure-140@4.[151,1435,453,1896]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1a–f. Chalcis boi sp. nov., holotype female: a, habitus, lateral, b, habitus, dorsal; c, head, frontal; d, head, lateral; e, protarsal claw; f, metafemur and metatibia, outer face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296701" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4296701/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="356">Fig. 1c</figureCitation>
); malar sulcus medially inconspicuous, straight, internal and external carinae fine and irregular, absent near eye; gena rugose, genal carina not reaching vertex; mandibular formula 2:3; antennal scrobe from coriaceous ventrally to slightly strigulate dorsally and with transverse carina below median ocellus (
<figureCitation box="[335,415,1614,1641]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1919,1943]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,453,1896]" captionTargetId="figure-140@4.[151,1435,453,1896]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1a–f. Chalcis boi sp. nov., holotype female: a, habitus, lateral, b, habitus, dorsal; c, head, frontal; d, head, lateral; e, protarsal claw; f, metafemur and metatibia, outer face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296701" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4296701/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="356">Fig. 1c</figureCitation>
); interantennal projection with median carina dorsally, carina extending midway to median ocellus. MOD:POL:APL:OOL = 0.21:0.48:0.36:0.17.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1038,2037]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1437,151,429]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="357" pageId="3" pageNumber="356">
<taxonomicName box="[199,319,1687,1712]" class="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" family="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" genus="Mesosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" pageId="3" pageNumber="356" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[199,319,1687,1712]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="356">Mesosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Mesoscutum with interstices coriaceous and dull, narrower than diameter of umbilicate foveae; mesoscutellum distinctly convex, frenal carina forming two sublateral lobes; mesopleuron with mesepisternum puncticulate-foveolate dorsally to irregularly areolate-rugulose ventrally, interstices coarsely coriaceous; propodeum with median carina well defined, submedian carina absent, anterior and posterior costulae irregular, adpetiolar area with irregular rugae medially, anterosubmedial area areolate-rugose (
<figureCitation box="[867,950,1830,1857]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1169,1193]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1145]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1435,181,1145]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2a–d. Chalcis boi sp. nov., holotype female: a, metatarsus, lateral; b, propodeum; c, gaster, lateral; d, ovipositor sheath, lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296703" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4296703/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="356">Fig. 2b</figureCitation>
); tarsomeres 4 and 5 of all legs with pubescence similar to other basal tarsomeres; protarsomeres 4 and 5 ventrally without pairs of distinct peg-like spines; protarsal claws only slightly curved, ventrally with 3 basal spines followed by 2 curved setae (
<figureCitation box="[1220,1300,1902,1929]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1919,1943]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,453,1896]" captionTargetId="figure-140@4.[151,1435,453,1896]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1a–f. Chalcis boi sp. nov., holotype female: a, habitus, lateral, b, habitus, dorsal; c, head, frontal; d, head, lateral; e, protarsal claw; f, metafemur and metatibia, outer face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296701" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4296701/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="356">Fig. 1e</figureCitation>
); mesocoxa densely pubescent posteriorly; mesotibial spur 0.3× as long as width of mesotibial apex; metacoxa punctate-rugose dorsally, inner face glabrous; metafemur with outer face very densely punctate and interstices weakly coriaceous to smooth and shiny, ventrally without inner basal tooth but with 10 teeth along outer margin, outer basal tooth the largest and distant from second tooth, the second tooth minute, the third to sixth teeth similar-sized (
<figureCitation box="[1259,1335,151,178]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1919,1943]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,453,1896]" captionTargetId="figure-140@4.[151,1435,453,1896]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1a–f. Chalcis boi sp. nov., holotype female: a, habitus, lateral, b, habitus, dorsal; c, head, frontal; d, head, lateral; e, protarsal claw; f, metafemur and metatibia, outer face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296701" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4296701/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="357">Fig. 1f</figureCitation>
); metatibia with apical spine robust and longer than apical width of metatibia (
<figureCitation box="[931,1008,187,214]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1919,1943]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,453,1896]" captionTargetId="figure-140@4.[151,1435,453,1896]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1a–f. Chalcis boi sp. nov., holotype female: a, habitus, lateral, b, habitus, dorsal; c, head, frontal; d, head, lateral; e, protarsal claw; f, metafemur and metatibia, outer face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296701" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4296701/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="357">Fig. 1f</figureCitation>
); metatarsomere 5 slightly longer than any of tarsomeres 1–4 (
<figureCitation box="[415,497,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1169,1193]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1145]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1435,181,1145]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2a–d. Chalcis boi sp. nov., holotype female: a, metatarsus, lateral; b, propodeum; c, gaster, lateral; d, ovipositor sheath, lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296703" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4296703/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="357">Fig. 2a</figureCitation>
). Fore wing SMV:MV:PMV = 1.86:0.74:0.83.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,429]" pageId="4" pageNumber="357">
<emphasis box="[199,316,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="357">Metasoma</emphasis>
