<figureCitation box="[996,1111,331,358]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1169,1193]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1145]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1435,181,1145]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2a–d. Chalcis boi sp. nov., holotype female: a, metatarsus, lateral; b, propodeum; c, gaster, lateral; d, ovipositor sheath, lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296703" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4296703/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="357">Figs 2c, d</figureCitation>
); ovipositor sheath obliquely truncate apically, with some long setae (
<figureCitation box="[600,684,367,394]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1169,1193]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1145]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[151,1435,181,1145]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2a–d. Chalcis boi sp. nov., holotype female: a, metatarsus, lateral; b, propodeum; c, gaster, lateral; d, ovipositor sheath, lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4296703" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4296703/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="357">Fig. 2d</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
